results.citation: Quinn T Ostrom, Mackenzie Price, Corey Neff, Gino Cioffi, Kristin A Waite, Carol Kruchko, Jill S Barnholtz-Sloan, CBTRUS Statistical Report: Primary Brain and Other Central Nervous System Tumors Diagnosed in the United States in 2015–2019, Neuro-Oncology, Volume 24, Issue Supplement_5, October 2022, Pages v1–v95, https://doi-org.dartmouth.idm.oclc.org/10.1093/neuonc/noac202
results.claim: Primary brain and other central nervous system tumors represent a significant burden on public health, with an average annual age-adjusted incidence rate of 24.71 per 100,000 population in the United States.

results.citation: Miller KD, Ostrom QT, Kruchko C, Patil N, Tihan T, Cioffi G, et al. Brain and other central nervous system tumor statistics, 2021. CA Cancer J Clin. 2021 Sept;71(5):381–406.
results.claim: Despite accounting for a small proportion of all malignancies, brain tumors contribute disproportionately to cancer-related morbidity and mortality due to their high fatality rates and the neurological sequelae associated with both the disease and its treatment.
